s=Step.new(recipe_id: 318, step: "make crust: Preheat oven to 350F. Stir crumbs 7 Tbsp melted butter 3 Tbsp brown sugar and nutmeg in medium bowl until blended then press firmly onto bottom and sides of a 9-inch springform pan. Wrap outside of pan with 3 layers of foil. Bake crust 12 minutes. Set aside to cool. make cheesecake: Beat cream cheese and brown sugar in a stand mixer until smooth. Beat in 1.5 tbsp whisky and 4 Tbsp of browned butter until blended. Beat in eggs 1 at a time until just blended. Pour mixture over crust. Place springform pan in large roasting pan. Add enough hot water to come halfway up sides of springform pan. Bake 1 hour 10 minutes cake until filling is puffed around edges and moves slightly in center when jiggled. Remove pan from water; remove foil. Place hot cheesecake uncovered in refrigerator overnight. make butterscotch sauce: Cook sugar corn syrup and 1/4 cup water in a small saucepan over medium heat stirring occasionally until sugar is dissolved. Increase heat and boil without stirring (brush down sides with a wet pastry brush to dissolve sugar crystals) 7-8 minutes until sauce is deep amber. Remove from heat and add cream and whiskey (it will bubble up). Whisk in remaining 2 Tbsp butter and salt and whisk until smooth. Cool to room temp. finish cheesecake: Spoon butterscotch sauce over top of cheesecake. Chill at least 2 hours. Run knife around pan sides to loosen cake; release pan sides. tip for browning butter: browning the butter for the cheesecake filling is easy. Melt the 4 tbsp butter in a small saucepan over medium heat. Cook and stir until butter stops foaming and browned bits form at bottom of pan stirring often about 5 minutes. cool to room temp.")
