s=Step.new(recipe_id: 322, step: "Step 1 Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. (325 degrees if dark pan). Grease and flour with baking spray then line with parchment paper a 9 x 3-inch heart shaped springform pan. Re-grease liner. Step 2 In an electric mixer beat the egg yolks with cup sugar until light and thick about 5 minutes. In a small bowl stir the water and extracts together until blended. Add to the yolk mixture slowly Step 3 Stir in the flour slowly until combined well. Step 4 Beat the egg whites until soft peaks form. Gradually add remaining sugar and beat until stiff and shiny peaks form. Add to the batter in 3 parts gently folding in the whites with a spatula. Step 5 Transfer batter to prepared pan. Bake until tester comes out clean about 30 minutes. Cool completely on rack. Step 6 Remove parchment paper cut cake in half. Place one half top side down onto plate. Spread the berry jam lightly and thinly over the cake layer. Arrange evenly 1 cup fresh berries over the jam layer. Step 7 Prepare the Ganache. Place chopped chocolate in a metal bowl. Bring cream to a boil pour over chopped chocolate. Let sit 1 minute then stir until chocolate is completely melted and smooth. Transfer of ganache to a small bowl cover and chill 20 minutes. Step 8 Place the second cake layer top side down on a rack sprayed with oil. Pour the unchilled chocolate ganache over top and sides of second layer. Smooth out very quickly to cover completely with an offset knife. Let set. Step 9 Beat the chilled Ganache a few minutes until it thickens. Spread evenly over thetop of the jam covered cake and sides. Then carefully transfer the previously Ganache-glazed cake layer evenly over the berry covered cake layer. Let set. Step 10 To decorate the cake arrange the small chocolate cookies around the edge of the heart cake. Place the berries in a heart shape in the center and arrange white chocolate balls around berries. Enjoy torte at room temperature.")
