s=Step.new(recipe_id: 323, step: "Step 1 Heat oven to 275 degrees. Line a baking sheet with waxed paper. Beat egg whites until foamy then beat in sugar and cocoa until stiff. Spread into three circles on waxed paper (can be made into heart shapes also). Bake 1 hour with oven door ajar. Cool completely. Place one of the meringues on a serving plate. Step 2 Prepare chocolate cream: In a small bowl stir sour cream with melted chocolate and powdered sugar. Spread over bottom meringue. Top with middle meringue. Step 3 Prepare Raspberry Cream: Beat ONE CUP of the whipped cream (reserving other two) with the jam and cream cheese. Spread over middle meringue then cover with final 3rd meringue. Top with remaining whipped cream and decorate with raspberries. (The top meringue can be piped into a lattice design if desired)")
