s=Step.new(recipe_id: 324, step: "FOR BUNDLES Step 1: Lay the bacon in a single layer in a shallow casserole dish. Step 2 Whisk the next 10 ingredients together and pour over the bacon. Step 3 Bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees. Step 4 Remove bacon from the casserole dish and roughly chop. Step 5 Saute bok choy in olive oil until just wilted but still verdant. Step 6 Gently fold the bacon bok choy chives and mango into the ricotta until thoroughly incorporated. Taste and salt/pepper as necessary. Then divide into 12 equal portions and roll into logs. *If the mixture is too soft to roll place in the fridge for about 30 minutes to firm up. Step 7 Melt the butter in a small saucepan. Step 8 Remove the phyllo from the fridge and lay it on top of a piece of plastic or parchment. Put another piece of plastic or parchment over the top of the phyllo and put a damp towel on top of that to keep the phyllo from drying out. With a pastry brush liberally brush some butter over the bottom of a baking sheet. Lay one sheet of phyllo down and brush it with butter. Fold the sheet of phyllo the long way and brush with butter again. Step 9 Put 1 bacon/ricotta log about 2 inches up from the bottom of the phyllo. Fold the bottom of the phyllo up over the entire thing and roll it all the way up to the other end. Tuck the ends under and put the bundle seam side down. Brush the top with butter. Sprinkle with sesame seeds. Now repeat the process for the remaining 11 bundles. Step 10 Place the bundles in a 350 degree oven for 10-15 minutes or until the tops of the bundles are beautifully browned. Serve immediately. FOR TARTARE: Step 1: Saute the pancetta until its crisp. Set aside. Step 2 Pour the tomatoes out of the cans into a colander and push on them gently to remove most of the liquid. Leave them in the colander while you make the rest of the dish so they can drain some more. Step 3 Beat the Dijon sun-dried tomato oil and extra virgin olive oil until emulsified. Add salt and pepper to taste. Step 4 Roughly chop the olives sun-dried tomatoes shallot chives and tarragon and put them in the food processor. Pulse til everything is pretty finely diced but not til its a paste. Transfer to the bowl with the dressing you just made. Step 5 Add teaspoon salt to the tomatoes and then add that to the bowl with the dressing and stuff from the food processor. Mix thoroughly and season to taste with salt and pepper. Step 6 Add all but 1 tablespoon of the pancetta (thats for garnish) to the mixture and mix thoroughly. Step 7 When ready to plate put a few tarragon leaves down make a quenelle of the tartare and put it on the tarragon leaves with just a bit of the green showing add a few pieces of chive to decorate and put a few pieces of pancetta right on the top.")
