s=Step.new(recipe_id: 326, step: "Step 1: Macerating the Strawberries Rinse and dry the strawberries. Remove the hulls and cut into 1/4 or 1/2 depending on how big they are. Place into a bowl and toss with sugar. Cover and refrigerate for a couple of hours. Step 2: Making the Strawberry Sour-Cream-Cheese Cake Take strawberries and run them through a food mill to remove the seeds using the fine steel disc. Set aside. In the bowl of a stand mixer add butter cream cheese sour cream and both sugars. Cream mixture together for 4 or 5 minutes. While the wet ingredients are creaming in the mixer in another bowl mix flour baking powder baking soda and salt together with a whisk. Set aside. When the mixture has creamed together sufficiently add the eggs and mix well. Add the vanilla and mix well. Add the strawberries and mix well. Once the strawberries are incorporated slowly add the flour mixture on low speed until everything is incorporated and smooth. Preheat oven to 350. Spray two loaf pans with cooking spray. Divide the dough evenly between the two pans. Bake for 60 minutes are until toothpick or skewer inserted into the center comes out clean. If the cakes are getting too brown before they are finished tent with foil. Start checking your cakes after 50 minutes of baking. When cakes are ready remove from oven and place on a cooling rack for 30 minutes. After 30 minutes run a knife along the edges and gently remove the cakes from the pans and allow to continue to cool completely. These are moist dense cakes almost like a pound cake or a dense bread and can be frozen. Wrap in plastic wrap and store in the refrigerator to keep them fresh. Step 3: Making the Sour-Cream-Cheese Spread In a medium bowl combine the cream cheese sour cream and brown sugar until it is smooth and completely mixed. Cover and refrigerate until ready to use. Step 4: Making the Whipped Cream For best results chill the beaters and bowl in the freezer for a half an hour before making the whipped cream. In a medium well chilled bowl add whipping cream sugar and vanilla and with an electric mixer beat on high until soft peaks form. Place in refrigerator until ready to use. Step 5A: Assembling the Dessert - Individual Plating Feeds up to 10 Cut the cake in 3/4 - 1 inch slices. Place each slice on a small plate. Next take the Sour-Cream-Cheese Spread and cover the top of the cake with 1 - 2 Tablespoons of the mixture spreading to the edges of the cake and about 1/4 inch thick. Repeat until all the slices are covered. Take the macerated strawberries and stir them to make sure the sugar and juices are coating the strawberries. Spoon a good size spoonful on top of each cake slice topped with the spread. Top each portion of strawberries with a dollop of whipped cream and serve. Step 5B: Assembling the Dessert - Potluck/Group Presentation Feeds up to 15 Cut both cakes in 1/2 horizontally. Take a 9 x 13 pan and place the slices next to each other cut side up until the bottom of the pan is completely covered with the cake in a single layer. You will probably have one layer or one half of one cake left over. Next take the Sour-Cream-Cheese Spread and cover the top of the cake with the mixture spreading to the edges of the cake and about 1/4 inch thick with a spatula. Take the macerated strawberries and stir them to make sure the sugar and juices are coating the strawberries. Spoon all of the strawberries and juice on top of the spread. Top the strawberries the whipped cream and serve.")
