s=Step.new(recipe_id: 329, step: "Step 1 Marinade Take 2lb tri-tip and poke several holes in it. Place first 5 ingredients into ziplock bag. Make sure marinade gets all over tri-tip. Marinade in refrigerator for at least an hour up to over night. Step 2 Smokey BBQ Aioli Place next 6 ingredients in a blender. Blend until smooth and combined. Set aside. Step 3 Dry Rub Once tri-tip is done marinading take out of bag and place on a plate. Mix next 7 ingredients for rub and sprinkle on all sides of tri-tip make sure to massage into meat. On high heat place meat on grill and cook 5-7 minutes on each side or until a nice char has formed. Turn heat to low and cook an additional 15 minutes. Remove from grill and let rest in foil for 10 minutes. Slice thin. Step 4 Caramelized Onions & Peppers While Tri-tip is cooking take onions peppers butter and oil and toss together in saut pan. Cook until nice and soft and slightly browning. Add worcestershire and cook until all liquid has been cooked off. Set these aside. Step 5 Toasting Bread & Melting Cheese Butter one side of each slice of bread. In a frying pan lay buttered side down. Once almost toasted place cheese on each slice. Cover with lid and allow cheese to melt. Remove from pan. Continue until all are done. Step 6 To Build Sandwich Take bottom slice with cheese and place about 1/4lb tr-tip. Spoon over the smokey bbq aioli place some caramelized onions and peppers on and top with top slice of bread with cheese. Enjoy! (have a fork and napkin handy might get messy!)")
