s=Step.new(recipe_id: 330, step: "Step 1: For ice cream heat oven to 425 degrees. Pour sweetened condensed milk into a 9-inch pie plate. Cover with heavy duty aluminum foil. Place pie plate in a larger pan then fill larger pan with 1/2-inch hot water surrounding pie plate. Bake for 75 minutes. Carefully remove from oven; remove pie plate from shallow pan. Whisk until smooth. Cool for 10 minutes. Step 2: Pour into a large shatterproof mixing bowl and place in freezer for 15 minutes. With mixer on low beat in extract and salt. Fold in whipped cream then whipped topping. Pour into a plastic or metal container. Cover and freeze for 4-6 hours or until firm. Step 3: For brownies reduce oven temperature to 350 degrees. Spray an 11x7-inch baking dish with cooking spray. Set aside. In a medium mixing bowl stir together sugar flour cocoa powder and salt. Use a wooden spoon to stir in melted butter eggs and extract until smooth. Spread evenly in prepared baking dish. Step 4: Bake for 25-30 minutes or until center is done. Remove from oven and cool completely before cutting into 12 brownies. Step 5: Just before serving place raspberries in a shallow bowl and sprinkle water evenly over top. Shake gently then sprinkle evenly with sugar. Shake gently again to evenly coat. Step 6: To serve stand two brownies in each sundae dish. Add about a -cup scoop of ice cream in center of each then top ice cream with cup of raspberries. Add a small dollop of whipped cream and a mint leaf on top of each for garnish. Step 7: Serve immediately. Serves 6.")
