s=Step.new(recipe_id: 332, step: "Step 1: Make the Peppermint Bark Line a large cookie sheet with parchment paper. In a large microwave safe bowl add the dark chocolate chips. Microwave on high heat for 30 seconds. Remove from the microwave add the peppermint extract and stir until combined until the chips are completely melted. Microwave for an additional 15 seconds if needed. Transfer the melted chips to the parchment paper and spread it out evenly with a rubber spatula. Transfer the sheet to the refrigerator for 10 minutes or until the chocolate is cool and hardened. In a separate bowl add the white chocolate chips. Microwave on high for 30 seconds remove and stir until the rest of the chips are melted. Microwave for an additional 15 seconds if needed. Spread the white chips evenly over the dark chocolate layer covering it completely. Then sprinkle the crushed candy canes on top of the melted white chips pressing down slightly on the candy pieces to set them into the white chocolate. Transfer the bark to the refrigerator for about 10-15 minutes until completely chilled and set. Remove from the refrigerator and use a kitchen mallet to break the bark up into various size pieces. Transfer the pieces back to the refrigerator to chill until ready to serve. Step 2: Make the Chocolate Mug Souffles Preheat the oven to 325 degrees. Butter the insides of four oven safe coffee mugs (at least 8 oz. each). Use a stand mixer with the whisk attachment to to whip the 4 egg whites on medium speed for about 2 minutes until they become frothy. Slowly add 2/3 cup of sugar and increase the mixing speed to medium-high. Whip for an additional 2-3 minutes until the mixture is twice its size. Turn off the mixer and add the 6 egg yolks one at a time mixing in between only enough to incorporate each egg yolk. Remove the bowl from the mixer and fold 1/2 cup of cocoa powder in with a rubber spatula. Transfer the batter to the buttered coffee mugs place them on a cookie sheet and bake at 325 degrees for about 30 minutes or until an inserted butter knife comes out clean. The souffls will have risen over the edges of the mugs but will fall shortly after being removed from the oven. Step 3: Plate and Serve Place each mug souffl on a medium serving dish. Brew the espresso and pour them into four individual 2 oz. shot glasses. Place the shot glasses on the serving dishes. Place 2-3 large pieces of peppermint bark into the souffls breaking them open and exposing the warm soft center. This will allow the bark to melt a bit. Serve the souffls and encourage the guests to pour the shot of espresso into the souffl before eating further melting the peppermint bark and flavoring the souffl while making it rich gooey and warm!")
