s=Step.new(recipe_id: 334, step: "Step 1: Prepare Chiles You want to start with burning the skin of the chiles over stovetop and place burned chile into any plastic bag. When all chiles are burned you want to peel off the burned skin. Make sure to try and NOT cut into the chile causing rips. Make a small slice on the top (stem end) of the chile to insert the the cut monteray jack cheese piece into the chiles. Set aside until ready to fry. Step 2: Prepare the sauce Prepare soup according to directions on can. Add the chopped onions cilantro and bell pepper. Let it cook on low flame. Take this time to heat up oil in large frying pan. Medium to high flame. Make sure oil is very hot before placing the chiles in pan. Step 3: Prepare the Egg Whites Place the egg whites in a large bowl and use a mixer on medium speed until you get a soft fluffy egg white. Than switch mixer to high until you get a stiff fluffy egg white. Add in the yolk while still mixing. By this time the oil should be hot enough and ready to fry the chiles. Step 4: Cooking the Chile Rellenos Dip the chiles into the stiff egg whites making sure the egg is covering the entire chile. Place immediately in the frying pan. Depending on the size of pan of course add as many chiles to fry at one time. Fry for about a minute on each side of chile. Just until the egg becomes a golden brown. Place chile relleno on plate and top with the cream mushroom sauce. Enjoy!")
