s=Step.new(recipe_id: 336, step: "Step 1: Preheat Oven and Cook Bacon Heat oven to 350 F degrees. Place bacon in microwave sandwiched between double sheets of paper towels. Microwave for 3 minutes on HIGH. If bacon is not crisp replace the paper towels and cook on HIGH at 30 second intervals until crisp. Set aside to cool on fresh paper towels. Step 2: Make Bourbon Cherry Filling In a large high-walled skillet over medium-high heat cook bourbon for 1 minute or until boiling. Reduce heat to medium and sugars and jam. Stir sauce constantly for 1-2 minute or until sugars have dissolved. Add lemon juice cornstarch and cherries. Cook for 1 minute over low heat stirring frequently. Divide cherries mixture into 6 buttered 8 oz. ramekin dishes. Step 3: Make Cobbler Combine flour baking powder baking soda and nutmeg in a medium bowl. In large mixing bowl combine butter and 1/2 cup sugar and beat until light and creamy about 2 minutes. Beat in eggs one at a time until fully incorporated. Slowly add flour mixture alternating with buttermilk just until combined but still lumpy. Fold in almonds. Spoon the batter on top of cherries leaving a little room for expansion. Step 4: Make Bacon Sugar and Bits Place 1/4 cup granulated sugar in a food processor and 3 slices of crispy bacon; pulse until finely ground bacon sugar forms. Sprinkle a generous amount over the batter. Crumble remaining bacon into bits and reserve to sprinkle on top after cobbler has baked. Step 5: Bake Cobbler Bake 25-30 minutes or until juices are bubbling and topping is golden and cooked through. Remove from oven crumble remaining bacon and sprinkle bacon bits on each cobbler. Step 6: Make French Vanilla Sauce and Serve Melt ice cream in a microwave safe dish on high heat for 30 seconds and drizzle on top of cobblers. Serve warm.")
