s=Step.new(recipe_id: 390, step: "Tomato Soup Heat oven to 400. Place tomatoes on oiled sheet tray and place in oven. Roast until skin is charred. (about 30 minutes). Melt butter in medium stockpot over medium heat. Cook onion and garlic (if using) stirring constantly until soft and translucent. (about 3 minutes). Add tomatoes their juices herbs and broth. Season with salt and pepper and bring to a boil then reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Use an immersion blender to puree tomato mixture and remove all solids. Return soup to clean pot and set over low heat. To serve top with a swirl of basil crema and croutons. Crema Plunge basil leaves and chives into a pot of rapidly boiling water for 30 seconds then shock in a prepared ice bath remove from ice bath and dry thoroughly. Blend ingredients for crema together in a blender and let stand one hour for flavors to meld. Parmesan Croutons Heat oven to 400 degrees F. Place the bread in a large bowl. Drizzle with the melted butter and toss well with Parmesan and seasonings. Spread out on a rimmed baking sheet and bake until golden about 10 minutes.")
