s=Step.new(recipe_id: 396, step: "Black Bean & Rice Patty Combine first 9 ingredients (black beans to lemon juice) and blend in food processor scraping down sides until nice and blended. Form into 4 pattys and set aside. Spicy Cabbage Salad Take the next 9 ingredients (rice vinegar to red curry paste) and blend together until smooth. Toss with cabbage and cucumber. Red Curry Sauce After the shredded cabbage take the next 11 ingredients (garlic to lemon zest) and heat in a sauce pan over medium heat until all are combined. Take some of this sauce and let the salmon marinade for 30 min. Set the rest of the sauce aside. Baking Pre-heat oven to 375. Place black bean and rice pattys on a baking sheet and drizzle with evoo and place in oven. Bake for 20-25 min or until tops have become slightly crispy. At the same time place the pre marinaded salmon on another baking sheet and place in oven. Bake for about 20 min or until flaky and opaque. To assemble place lay patty down top with salmon. Squeeze lemon wedge and spoon over more red curry sauce. Top with spicy cabbage and sprinkle cilantro over top. Enjoy!")
