s=Step.new(recipe_id: 422, step: "Preheat oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit. In a large mixing bowl cream butter and sugar. Add eggs one at a time beating well after each addition. Beat in vanilla. Combine in a separate bowl the flour cocoa baking powder and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture and mix well. Stir in the coarsely-crushed cookies. Spread into a greased 9x13 pan. Bake for 25-30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool in a pan on a wire rack. Frosting In a mixing bowl beat the powdered sugar and butter. Add vanilla. Gradually add the milk until desired consistency is achieved. Frost the cooled brownies with the buttercream and sprinkle with the finely-crushed Oreo crumbs.")
