s=Step.new(recipe_id: 434, step: "Preheat convection oven to 425. Peel and wash potatoes. Slice horizontally into four thin sections. Take two sections and lay them flat slicing into three or four French fry slices. Repeat with second section and rest of potatoes. Rinse in cool water and dry thoroughly with a towel. Sprinkle liberally with salt and pepper or seasoning of choice (Greek seasoning is great!). Drizzle with olive oil and toss to coat. Spray baking sheet with cooking spray and spread potatoes over tray. Place into hot oven and bake for 15-20 minutes or until browned on both sides.")
s.save!
s=Step.new(recipe_id: 435, step: "step 1 Preheat oven to 350. Line a 12 count regular muffin pan with paper liners. Graham Cracker Cupcakes Combine finely ground cracker crumbs flour baking powder and cinnamon in a bowl. In a large bowl beat 3/4 cup butter and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla. Add 1/2 the buttermilk and 1/2 the cracker mixture. Repeat with remaining milk and cracker mixture. Spoon mixture into muffin cups (3/4 full) Bake until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean about 20-22 minutes. Marshmallow Filling Whip cream cheese until smooth. Add marshmallow creme and beat on low just until combined. Fold whipped cream into marshmallow mixture. Refrigerate until ready to use. Chocolate Ganache Place chocolate in a small bowl. In a small saucepan heat 1/2 cup heavy cream and 1 tablespoon butter over medium until butter is melted and mixture starts to boil. Remove from heat and immediately pour over chocolate. Allow to sit for one minute and then stir until melted and smooth. Cool. Spiced and Loaded Pecans In a saucepan over medium heat combine brown sugar half and half and butter. Once sauce is starting to bubble reduce heat to low and add brandy and cayenne. Continue to simmer sauce stirring frequently 6 to 8 minutes or until it starts to thicken. Remove from heat and stir in pecans. Refrigerate sauce until it becomes somewhat firm so nuts can be spooned onto cupcakes. To assemble: Place marshmallow filling into pastry bag with a cupcake tip. Gently press tip into center of cupcake and squeeze bag. Pipe some filling into center of cupcake and then finish with swirl of filling on top. Drizzle or pipe chocolate ganache onto top of filling and finish cupcake with a spoonful of spiced nuts.")
s.save!
s=Step.new(recipe_id: 436, step: "Step 1 Preheat Broiler. Toss 2 jalapenos and 3 cloves garlic in 1 Tbsp olive oil. Set in baking dish. Place in broiler for 10-15 or until tender. Step 2 Blend together juice from 2 limes chipotles adobo sauce 2 cloves garlic 1 tsp salt and cumin in a food processor. Pour marinade over filet and wrap tight. Set in refrigerator to marinade for at least 30 minutes. Step 3 Meanwhile begin the salsa: Chop onion tomato bunch cilantro and 1 jalapeno. Place in small bowl. Mince garlic. Add to mixture. Add juice 1 lime and remaining salt. Blend thoroughly. Refrigerate until ready to use Step 4 Prepare the Jalapeno Avocado Aioli: In a blender place the roasted jalapenos and garlic avocado mayo tsp salt and 1 Tbsp lime juice. Blend until smooth and all ingredients are fully incorporated. Refrigerate until ready to use (but at least 20 minutes) Step 5 Heat 2 Tbsp olive oil in large skillet over medium heat. Add filets once oil is hot and cook for 5 minutes. Turn and continue cooking for 3 minutes. Step 6 While fish is finishing cooking slice each roll in half almost to end. Hand shred the arugula and tear cilantro off stems. Toss both greens together. Step 7 Once fish is cooked build sandwiches: Into each roll place 1 filet top with a handful of the greens mixture top with 2-3 Tbsp salsa and top with about 2-3 Tbsp aioli.")
s.save!
s=Step.new(recipe_id: 437, step: "Prepare Your Pumpkin Cut a small pumpkin in half scoop out the seeds and remove the stringy fibers in the hollow. Place the two halves in a roasting pan skin side up and fill pan with a cup of water. Put the pumpkin into an over preheated to 350F for about 90 minutes. Once the pumpkin is cool enough to work with scoop the meat out of each half and discard the skin. Puree the pumpkin meat in a food processor (or blender). This should yield about 3 - 4 cups of pumpkin puree. Youll have enough for this pumpkin recipe and a few more. Itll keep for 4 days refrigerated. On the Stove In a large saut pan heat 3 tablespoons of butter once the butter has melted and begins to bubble add the onion and garlic stir and add salt once onion becomes translucent add thyme allspice and fresh ground pepper. This will soak up the butter keep stirring then deglaze the pan using about half of the orange juice. Be sure to get all the little bits off the bottom of the pan and reduce the heat. On a low temperature add in the pumpkin. Then slowly add the shredded cheeses (reserving just a pinch of each) while constantly stirring add in the rest of the butter and orange juice to keep the mixture from thickening too much. In the Oven Once the cheeses have thoroughly melted and blended with the pumpkin -- transfer to a ceramic baking dish and finish dip by sprinkling remaining cheese on top and melting it in a 350 oven. For parties triple this recipe and stuff a hollowed out small pumpkin with the dip. Serve with pita or tortilla chips.")
s.save!
s=Step.new(recipe_id: 438, step: "Step 1 - Preparing the meat Season brisket with special rub consisting of Hungarian paprika black pepper onion powder garlic power and additional ingredients (since I am in the process of marketing the rub I can not disclose full ingredient list). Step 2 - Braising the beef Braise brisket for 6-12 hours on low heat (oven temperature should be between 225 - 250 degrees) Step 3 - Prepare the Cole Slaw As meat is cooking prepare homemade cole slaw. Mix together mayonnaise mustard and relish with onions shredded cabbage (green and red mixture) as well as carrot. (You may also use pre-packaged shredded veggies in the interest of time). Stir mixture. Add in sugar and continue stirring until mixture is wet but not soupy. Salt and pepper to taste. Refrigerate mixture to allow flavors to meld. Step 4 - Prepare the BBQ Sauce Prepare the homemade barbecue sauce by combing the following ingredients in a blender and mixing until you have thick smooth consistency: ketchup vinegar garlic cloves red onions onion powder mustard powder fresh ground pepper lemon juice brown sugar white sugar Worchestshire sauce and a dash of my special rub Add water if you wish to have a thinner consistency Step 5 - Rest the meat When the brisket is done allow the meat to cool. Slice the fatback off Step 6 - Plating To plate: Carve the brisket into slider portion size (or full sandwich size). Place on sweet potato roll Spoon 2 tablespoons of cole slaw onto the brisket Top with a tablespoon or two of the barbecue sauce Add a handful of crispy onion straws on top *May also include a slice of gouda cheese in the sandwich")
s.save!
s=Step.new(recipe_id: 439, step: "Step 1 As a general rule I start with a quarter cup of mayo a few squeezes of fresh lime juice a little pinch of kosher salt and one and a half to two chipotle peppers with a little spoonful of the adobo sauce from the can. If its too spicy for you just add a little more mayo. If its not spicy enough add more chile with a little squeeze of lime juice. Step 2 There are three ways you can mix it all together: a food processor a hand blender or just chop the chile very finely and mix in by hand. Step 3 I typically will blend the chipotles salt and lime juice together first in a food processor or blender but theres no wrong way to do it. In the end you just want to make sure that the mayo is blended smoothly with the chile mixture. There shouldnt be any chunks of chile in it and the mayo should be a reddish-orange speckled hue.")
s.save!
s=Step.new(recipe_id: 440, step: "Bacon Brine & Maple Smoke 1. In a small bowl combine the remaining mustard seed and coriander with the maple syrup bourbon and salt. 2. Pour the marinade in the bag and massage it into the pork belly. Press the air out of the plastic bag and seal. 3. Refrigerate for at least 24 hours up to 3 days; remix and turn the bag over occasionally. 4. Prepare the smoker to cook at 225-250 degrees. When the coals are ready throw in the wood chips. 5. Remove the pork butt from the marinade and set up on the grill fat side up over a drip pan. Close the smoker and let it go for at least 2 hours before peeking in on it. 6. Keep the temperature of the smoker around 200 degrees. Smoke the pork belly until the internal temperature reaches at least 150. Prepare Pork Belly 7. Prepare the Marinated Smoked Pork Belly 8. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees 9. In an oven proof dish add the smoked pork belly along with garlic ginger black peppercorns soy sauce rice wine vinegar and chicken broth. 10. Place it in the oven and let it get braised for 2 hours. Remove dry the pork belly and cool. 11. Take the pork belly and score criss cross patterns with a sharp knife on the top surface. 12. Slice the pork belly block into smaller blocks. 13. Heat a pan with the olive oil. 14. Add the smoked pork belly blocks in it and fry it until crisp and brown on top. Prepare Bacon Fried Rice Base 15. In a large non-stick skillet or wok over medium-high heat cook bacon until it is browned and fat is rendered about 10 minutes. Drain any excess fat from pan (you still want a thin layer coating the bottom) and push bacon to sides of pan. 16. In the center add onions and cook until softened about 2 minutes. 17. Stir in green onions garlic and ginger and cook for 3 minutes taking care not to let the garlic brown. 18. Stir in peas and cook for 2 minutes or until warm. Transfer the mixture to a medium bowl. 19. Lower heat to medium cook quail eggs over easy for 2-3 minutes or until fully cooked. Put quail eggs to the side. Wipe out skillet (careful as it may be hot) add vegetable oil and return to medium-high heat. When oil is hot but not smoking add cooked rice and spread in an even layer. Cook stirring occasionally for 5 minutes or until rice is heated through and slightly crispy. 20. Stir in bacon-egg mixture. Season to taste with soy sauce. Prepare Praline Bacon Toping 21. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F. 22. Place a wire rack on a sheet tray. Combine the Pecans and brown sugar. Lay the 6 Strips of bacon side by side on the rack place in the preheated oven for about 15-20 minutes or until the bacon is sizzling and starting to brown around the edges. The object is for the bacon to cook about 3/4 of the way through before adding the topping. 23. Push the partially cooked bacon as close together as possible on the rack and brush with the dark corn syrup this will give the topping something to grab on to. 24. Cover generously with the Pecan/brown sugar topping. Place back in the oven for about 10 minutes more or until the topping is bubbly and the bacon is good and brown. Let cool. 25. As the Praline Bacon cools it will set up and have a nice chewy bite to it. Bacon Gazpacho Combine : 3 fully cooked bacon strips plum tomatoes bell pepper red pepper cucumber green onions cilantro jalapeo chili and tomato juice in a large bowl and refrigerate overnight. In a blender puree the vegetables until smooth. Strain the soup into a deep bowl season with salt and pepper and serve.")
s.save!
s=Step.new(recipe_id: 441, step: "Step 1 I used my Kenmore Elite food processor for this recipe. Begin by chilling the whipping cream in the freezer for up to an hour making sure to shake the container every 10-15 minutes so that the cream doesnt freeze completely. Its perfectly fine if ice crystals form along the sides or the cream gets little ice chunks in it when you pour it into the food processor. Pour it in and secure the food processor top. Step 2 Run the processor for about a minute or two then add the 2 teaspoons of granulated sugar. Keep running the processor for another minute or two. You may want to stop the motor briefly and open the lid to make sure that the cream is beginning to thicken. If necessary use a spatula to push any whipped cream down the wall of the bowl. Step 3 Turn the processor back on and let it run for about 30 seconds. Begin to slowly add the cajeta. I prefer about 2 tablespoons so its not as sweet but you can add up to 3 tablespoons if you like. Run the processor until the cajeta is incorporated. Unplug your food processor and use a rubber spatula to spoon the whipped cream out of the bowl. You can serve immediately or store in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 2 days.")
s.save!
s=Step.new(recipe_id: 442, step: "step 1 Combine milk shortening sugar and salt. Cool to lukewarm in large bowl step 4 Divide the dough into 5 equal pieces and keep covered to prevent drying step 5 Combine the walnuts and brown sugar and set aside step 7 Bake at 350 for 20 minutes (about 3 rolls will fit on a standard baking sheet)")
s.save!
s=Step.new(recipe_id: 443, step: "For the dough Place shortening sugar and salt in a large bowl. Pour hot milk over and allow shortening to melt. Add beaten egg and yeast-water mixture. Stir to combine. Add flour. Stir vigorously to combine. Cover and allow to rise for 2 hours. Turn dough out onto a well-floured surface. Knead for 10 minutes. Allow to rest/relax for 10 minutes. Roll dough out into a rectangle of about - inch thickness. Spread margarine over the entire surface. For the filling Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Combine 1 bag cranberries c. sugar zest of one orange c orange juice 2 TBSP cornstarch in a 2 qt sauce pan. Cook over medium heat until thick. Use a whisk to stir and mash cranberries. Remove from heat and allow to cool before using. Spread over cinnamon-sugar-butter coating. Roll up as you would a jelly roll. Place on a pizza pan or cookie sheet. Form into a circle/wreath and tuck ends together. Using kitchen shears snip 1 cuts around the entire ring. Using your fingers turn each dough cut under to expose the cinnamon layer. Bake at 375 degrees for 25 minutes. Allow to cool slightly before removing from pan. Allow to cool before frosting. For the frosting Mix ingredients in a bowl. Pour icing into a piping or Ziploc bag. Snip the end and drizzle over the entire tea ring.")
s.save!
s=Step.new(recipe_id: 444, step: "For the Pico de gallo In bowl combine the tomato onion jalapeo lime juice and zest and the cilantro. Mix well. Adjust seasoning with salt and pepper. Set aside until ready to use. For the Queso Fundido Preheat oven to 400. In cast iron skillet(or ovenproof pan) cook bacon until browned and crispy - about 5 minutes. Remove to paper towel lined plate and set aside until ready to use. Remove all but 1 tablespoon of the bacon fat and add the onion poblano and jalapeo. Season with salt and pepper. Cook on medium high stirring often until veggies are softened and beginning to brown - about 8 minutes. Add the garlic and beans and continue cooking about 2 more minutes. Sprinkle the pickled jalapeo over top of the bean mixture. Sprinkle the cheese overtop evenly. Place skillet in oven and bake until the cheese is bubbly and browned - about 10 minutes. Remove from oven and top with the bacon and pico de guillo. Eat with the warmed tortillas!")
