s=Step.new(recipe_id: 448, step: "Step 1 Drain and rinse black beans or garbanzo beans. Step 2 Prep veggies (onion bell pepper mushrooms and carrot). Step 3 Heat coconut oil in a skillet. Step 4 Add fresh garlic onions and bell pepper. Cook for 3 minutes. Step 5 Now add mushrooms and spices. Cook for another 3 minutes. Step 6 Turn off heat and transfer this mixture into a food processor. Step 7 Add black or garbanzo beans and pulse for a few seconds. (you dont want a mushy consistency...keep it rustic and chunky). Step 8 Transfer into a mixing bowl and fold in shredded carrots and walnuts. Section 9 Mold mixture into 4 patties. Step 10 Heat oil in same skillet and then add burger patties. Step 11 Cook on each side for 3-4 minutes on medium high heat. Step 12 Transfer to a plate. Step 13 Now add butter to the skillet and pan fry the bread slices until golden and crisp. Step 14 Spread raspberry preserve onto a slice of bread. Layer with spinach leaves. Then top with bean patty. Now add cheese slice and complete with second slice of bread. Step 14 Plate the burger cut it in half and enjoy!")
