s=Step.new(recipe_id: 531, step: "Directions: For seasoned butter: Mix all ingredients with fork in medium bowl. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and refrigerate. Bring to room temperature before using.) For the Sea Bass: Sprinkle with salt and pepper and cook in 1 tablespoon of oil until golden on both sides. Finish in a preheated oven for about 5 minutes. Cover with foil to hold. For the potatoes: Add potatoes and garlic to cold water with salt and boil until tender. About 15 minutes. Drain and put back into pot with butter cream salt and pepper. Mash and cover until ready to serve. Cook down the fennel in 1 tablespoon of the fennel butter To serve: Place potatoes on the bottom of a plate top with sea bass a dollop of fennel butter and fennel. Garnish with fennel fronds.")
