s=Step.new(recipe_id: 552, step: "Directions: 1. Pour boiling water over vermicelli rice noodles and soak 15 minutes. Drain and rinse. Divide into 8 equal portions. Fill a wide shallow bowl with cool water. Working with one spring-roll wrapper at a time soak until pliable 20 seconds. Transfer to a flat surface and smooth. 2. Place a layer of fillings on bottom third of wrapper leaving a 1 1/2-inch border. Top with a portion of noodles and another layer of fillings. 3. Fold bottom of wrapper tightly over fillings. 4. Roll over once tuck in sides and finish rolling. Transfer roll to a plate and cover with a slightly damp paper towel. Repeat to make 8 summer rolls. Serve immediately with dipping sauce or refrigerate up to 2 hours.")
