s=Step.new(recipe_id: 558, step: "Step 1 Pour oil into a deep fryer or large heavy pot and heat to 375 degrees F. In a medium mixing bowl combine the cornmeal flour salt baking powder and baking soda. In a separate bowl combine the corn onion and buttermilk. Add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients all at once and stir only enough times to bring the batter together; there should be lumps. Set batter aside and allow to rest for 10 minutes. Step 2 Scatter the cornstarch into a dry pie pan. Roll each cocktail wiener in the cornstarch and tap well to remove any excess. Step 3 Scatter the cornstarch into a dry pie pan. Roll each cocktail wiener in the cornstarch and tap well to remove any excess. Step 4 To make the sauce Heat the oil in a saucepan over medium heat. Stir in the onion garlic cayenne brown sugar and fennel seeds and cook until onion is tender and sugar has melted. Mix in ketchup and soy sauce. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer 10 minutes. Serve along side the corn dogs. Enjoy!!")
