s=Step.new(recipe_id: 601, step: "Step 1: In a large mixing bowl combine eggs oil parsley salt and pepper for 2 minutes. Add in matzo meal then slowly add in soda water till combined. Step 2: Fill a large pot with water and bring to a simmer. With wet hands roll out 1-ounce balls (about the size of a walnut). Add balls to water and simmer until tender light and fluffy in the center 30-45 minutes. (To test centers insert a toothpick which should slide easily all the way through.) While matzo balls are cooking in a large dutch oven rub the garlic clove over the inside of the pot and discard the clove. Add in stock boullion carrots and celery. Cook for 20 minutes. Right before the matzo balls are finished add in the diced chicken to the chicken soup mixture. When matzo balls are finished drain and add to chicken soup. Serve with fresh dill.")
