s=Step.new(recipe_id: 621, step: "Step 1 Fill a large pot about 3/4 full of water and set on burner on high. Add the 12 boullion cubes. Add the chopped potatoes and carrots. In a large bowl crumble the ground beef. Add 3-4 Tbls of diced green onion and 3-4 Tbls of cilantro to the ground beef and add the same to the soup pot. Add minced garlic and about 1/2 C rice; add remaining 1/4 C rice to soup pot. Add salt and pepper and garlic powder to taste (about 2 tsp each). I just eyeball it. Add the two eggs and then mix to combine all the ingredients. Start forming meatballs (about 1 inch) and drop them into the soup pot. Add 1 can green beans and 1 can corn drained to the pot. Add 1 can fire roasted tomatoes (Ive used stewed tomatoes too). Add diced mushrooms broccoli and zucchini. Add salt and pepper and garlic powder to pot (again about 1-2 tsp to taste). Add 1/3 C lemon juice to pot. Soup should be boiling by now. Turn down between medium and medium-high and let cook for about 45 minutes or until rice is tender in the meatballs. Serve with lemon wedges to squeeze in each bowl and diced Serrano Chiles (optional).")
