s=Step.new(recipe_id: 622, step: "Pre-cook Yams and Apricots Cook yams in water till tender about 25 minutes. Drain cool and peel. Mash slightly with hand-held potato masher. While yams are cooking bring dried apricots to boil in small amount of water over low heat. For moist apricots use about cup water. Very dry apricots will need up to 2 cups. Simmer till apricots are rehydrated about 10 minutes. Stir frequently breaking up apricots with a wooden spoon. Remove from heat and mash apricots with a potato masher. Prepare Egg Mixture Beat eggs until fluffy. Beat in sugar salt and Grand Marnier. Puree and Combine Ingredients Puree yams with immersion blender or electric mixer on medium speed. Add apricots. If apricots are in large chunks continue using blender or mixer to break them up. Stir in melted and cooled butter. Add egg mixture and orange peel to yam mixture and stir together with mixer or by hand. Stir in 3/4 teaspoon cinnamon. Bake Casserole Turn into buttered 9 x 13 (3 quart) casserole dish. Sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon or to taste. Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325 degrees F. Garnish Casserole Slice orange into rounds or other shapes. Garnish casserole with orange shapes and mint leaves or parsley.")
