s=Step.new(recipe_id: 629, step: "Step 1-base 1 stick butter & 1 cup flour-work by hand Add 1 T cold water Form ball and divide in two. Make 2-12 inch rolls and flatten into desired shapes on cookie sheet with palm of hand. Step 2-top In pan together 1 cup water & 1 stick butter. Bring to boil. Remove from heat and add 1 cup flour And 1 T almond extract. Beat in 3 eggs one at a time by spoon. Spread on above mixture. Step 3-bake Bake about 1 hour at 350 degrees. Cool. Frost. Decorate. Step 4-frost & decorate Frosting 1 cup powdered sugar 2 T softened butter or margarine teaspoon vanilla 1 teaspoon almond extract Add 2-3 teaspoons milk. Mix and add coloring. Top with any candy nuts or creative confection you want. In the photo above we used M & M candy in holiday colors alternating with slivered almonds and sprinkles. ENJOY!")
