s=Step.new(recipe_id: 630, step: "See Below Ingredients: * 5 cups diced cornbread - Martha Whie/Jiffy * 4 cups diced white/wheat bread * 2 ounces butter * 2 cups onion chopped * 1 TBSP Minsed Garlic * 3 to 4 cups Vegetable Broth * Half Packet Mushroom Gravy Mix * 1 teaspoon salt * 1/2 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper * 3 eggs lightly beaten (Can Substitute Egg Substitute) Preparation: Heat oven to 375F. In a large mixing bowl combine the cornbread and white/wheat bread cubes. In a saucepan over medium heat saut the onions and garlic in butter until tender. Do not brown. Combine the sauted vegetables with the bread mixture. Stir in vegetable broth using enough to moisten. Stir in the seasonings gravy mix and beaten eggs blending well. Spread the mixture in a large shallow baking or roasting pan measuring about 10 x 15. Bake for 25 to 35 minutes. Note deeper pans will take longer cooking times. Mixture should be firm to touch brown but moist inside when done. (Note onions can be lightly cooked in the microwave rather than adding butter to the recipe).")
