s=Step.new(recipe_id: 631, step: "Marinade the Chicken In a small bowl whisk together oil garlic cinnamon caraway seeds cumin cardamom and cayenne pepper. Place chicken in a large resealable plastic bag set in a shallow dish. Add oil mixture. Press air from bag; seal. Cover and chill for 8 to 24 hours turning bag occasionally. Cook The Chicken Place chicken in a 4- to 5-quart slow cooker. In a medium bowl combine broth apricots dates ground almonds turmeric salt pepper and saffron; pour over chicken. Cover and cook on low-heat setting for 8 hours or on high-heat setting for 4 hours. Serve the Chicken Use a slotted spoon to remove chicken mixture from slow cooker (some meat may fall off the bone); place chicken in a shallow serving dish. Sprinkle chicken with cilantro and sliced almonds. Skim fat from cooking liquid. Serve chicken with cooking liquid and if desired couscous.")
