s=Step.new(recipe_id: 634, step: "Step 1: Prep the Vegetables Prepare all of the vegetables before browning the ground beef. This allows for a smooth cooking process only involving one person cooking. Leave the vegetables on the cutting board until it is time to place them into the pot. Step 2: Brown the Meat Coat the bottom of the pot with extra virgin olive oil then place the pound of lean ground beef into the pot. Brown the meat thoroughly. Hint: If youre a person who doesnt like a lot of fat in their meals like myself sprinkle some salt onto the ground beef to release some of those fatty juices so they may be poured into something disposable like an empty can. DO NOT POUR THE FAT/GREASE DOWN THE DRAIN IT MAY CLOG YOUR PIPES ONCE IT COOLS DOWN! Step 3: Adding the Vegetables The first vegetable you will want to add to the pot once the meat is browned is the diced green peppers. Green peppers are hard and crunchy so you will want to saute them in the meat first. Wait about 5 to minutes to add the other ingredients while continuing to stir the peppers. Add the sliced squash and zucchini after that time since they have about the same consistency. Add the halved olives into the pot as well. It is very important to add the olives in the beginning stages of this spaghetti sauce because black olives can be kind of squeaky if they are under cooked in the sauce. Let the vegetables sit to saute while being covered occasionally stirring for about 8-10 minutes. Be sure to include the garlic salt and Italian seasonings to the meat and vegetable mixture. Add any other spices deemed necessary. Step 4: Add the Sauce For this recipe I chose not to use a bottle of spaghetti sauce because I am creating my own. This is very important for people who have a gluten allergy it allows them to know EXACTLY what is going into this spaghetti. Add the tomato paste to the vegetables and beef. Add the two cans of tomato sauce (they typically look like little half cans). Add the can of diced tomatoes (the tomatoes may be accompanied by green chilies onions or just by themselves your call). Stir all of that deliciousness up and let it sit covered for about 10 minutes. Dont forget to stir! At first it may look as though there is not enough sauce for all of those vegetables but just wait everything will cook down and it will be plenty. Step 5: Spaghetti Time! Begin to boil the water for the spaghetti. The sauce is done so move it to the burner behind it to let it cool. In this recipe Ive used an all natural vegetable spaghetti noodle so that it doesnt contain any gluten. Look at the ingredients to the pasta noodles and if any say durum or semolina they contain gluten so put those down. I found these noodles at my local Kroger but they typically have them at any natural food store. If youre a person who cant find these special noodles just use regular ones; recipes are all about substitutions. Cook the noodles until done and enjoy The Famous Spaghetti!!")
s.save!
