s=Step.new(recipe_id: 640, step: "Step 1 Wash potatoes and wrap in aluminum foil. Bake on 400 for 50 minutes cool. Lower oven temp to 375. Step 2 Chop peppers and onion into nickel size pieces. Unwrap potatoes and slice with skin on. Potatoes may crumble a bit but that is okay. Slice sausage at a diagonal about 1/4 inch thick. You can adjust the thickness and chunk sizes to your taste if needed. Step 3 Pour oil into a large bowl. Add salt pepper cumin garlic powder cilantro and paprika to the oil and mix well. Add all prepared ingredients and toss. Pour onto a foil lined baking sheet and spread out so that everything is even. Step 4 Bake for 15-25 minutes (depending on your oven) or until hash is golden brown and crisp tender. Serve immediately with buttermilk cornbread.")
