s=Step.new(recipe_id: 641, step: "Step 1 Step 1: In a large heavy Dutch oven brown bacon; with a slotted spoon transfer to a medium bowl; add brat and brown in rendered bacon fat; with a slotted spoon transfer to cooked bacon bowl; set aside. Step 2 Add bell peppers celery onion. jalapeno and garlic to pan and saut in remaining bacon fat till slightly browned stirring occasionally (about 10 minutes); return bacon brat and remaining ingredients to pan except for cheese buns butter and chives; simmer over medium/low heat for about 45 minutes. Step 3 Meanwhile pre-heat oven (or toaster oven) to 375 degrees F. Meanwhile with a serrated knife cut off pretzel bun tops; carefully scoop out inside dough forming a bowl; lay pretzel bun bowls and tops over a sheet pan and brush sides and tops with butter; bake in pre-heated oven for 3-5 minutes or till crust is slightly toasted; remove buns; reserve tops. Step 4 Once chili has simmered for 45 minutes add 1 cup white cheddar cheese to hot chili and combine well; fill pretzel bowls with chili; top with 1 Tbsp cheese; garnish with chives and place bread top on the side.")
