s=Step.new(recipe_id: 647, step: "Step 1 Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Butter (or spray with nonstick spray) a 9-inch springform pan. Line bottom with parchment and butter that as well. Wrap outside of pan with foil. In a medium sauce pan over low heat stir chocolate and butter until smooth; remove from heat to cool slightly. Step 2 Beat egg yolks and HALF the sugar for 3 minutes until pale. Fold in lukewarm chocolate mixture vanilla and chopped bacon. In another bowl beat egg whites with clean dry beaters until soft peaks form. Beat in remaining half of sugar until medium stiff peaks form; fold into chocolate mixture. Pour into prepared pan and bake 50 minutes. Cool in pan. Cake will fall; this is okay. Step 3 Press crumbly edges of cake (still in pan) down to form a level top. Run knife around sides to loosen then remove sides. Invert onto serving plate. Peel off parchment. Cut in half horizontally and drizzle caramel over what is now the bottom layer to form filling. Top with other cake half. Make glaze: Simmer cream and corn syrup in a small sauce pan then remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips until smooth. Pour over cake then chill one hour until glaze is firm. Can be made a day ahead but serve at room temperature.")
