s=Step.new(recipe_id: 648, step: "step 1 Spray 8 inch springform pan with cooking spray. Heat oven to 350 degrees step 2 Unroll puff pastry onto a lightly floured parchment paper or counter top. Press pastry with floured fingertips until creases are removed and pastry fits into pan. Gently press pastry into the sprayed springform pan and press pastry up sides of pan to form 2 inch crust or tart shell. step 3 Break goat cheese into small pieces and place in bottom of shell. Top with sliced pears. step 4 In a small bowl beat eggs and sugar about 1 minute. Add flour cream and vanilla. Gently pour mixture over pears. Bake for 45 minutes at 350 degrees. Citrus-Ginger Glaze In a small saucepan over medium heat combine orange marmalade honey ginger and 2/3 cup water. Bring to a boil and reduce heat to low. Simmer about 3-5 minutes or until mixture reduces by . Cool slightly. Brush top of clafouti with glaze. Serve clafouti warm with remaining glaze. Makes 8 servings")
s.save!
s=Step.new(recipe_id: 649, step: "Directions for Smoked Ribs: Combine the salt pepper and garlic powder. Rub ribs on both sides with the rub mixture. Smoke the ribs for 6 hours or until ribs have pulled up the bone by about an inch up the bone. I recommend using Oak wood. When ribs are done pull off the smoker. If you arent making the chili in the same day store ribs in refrigerator until you want to make the chili. Directions for Chili: While the ribs are smoking you can roast the poblano anaheim and red peppers on a gas stovetop grill or in the oven turning until all sides are blistered and blackened. Remove from heat and place in a bowl covered with plastic wrap and let cool. When cooled remove the skin from the peppers. Chop the peppers into 1/2-inch pieces and set aside. Heat a large stockpot over medium heat. Add the oil. When stockpot is heated add the red onion stirring occasionally until softened. Season with salt and pepper as needed. Add garlic and cook 1 minute. Next add beer beef stock roasted peppers fire roasted tomatoes tomato sauce tomato paste and black beans and stir until combined. Stir in garlic powder onion powder chipotle chili powder oregano dried aji dulce or sumac sugar and cumin. Stir once again to combine. Add in short rib meat when it is finished and bring to a boil. Once boiling lower heat to a simmer. Simmer at least 3 hours to combine flavors. When chili is done pull out the ribs. Remove the meat from the bones and any non-meat components of the ribs like the skin from the underside of the rack. Place the meat shredded and pulled from the bones back into chili stir to combine and serve. Notes: *You can substitute the Vanilla-Fig Balsamic by taking 1 TBSP Sugar with 1/4 cup Balsamic Vinegar Combine two in a small pan until reduce by half. Let cool to room temperature and add 1/2 TBSP Vanilla Extract. Stir to combine and use in recipe")
s.save!
s=Step.new(recipe_id: 650, step: "step 1 Cook pasta according to package direction. step 2 Saut mushrooms and garlic in olive oil over medium heat until mushrooms are tender. Add peppercorns and chicken broth. Continue to cook until mixture is hot and starts to bubble. Reduce heat to low. step 3 In a small bowl stir flour into cream until all lumps are dissolved. Slowly add mixture to mushrooms. Add brandy and continue to cook until mixture starts to thicken. Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice. Serve sauce over cooked pasta. Topping In a small bowl combine pecans feta and basil. Add tomatoes if desired. Sprinkle over sauce")
s.save!
s=Step.new(recipe_id: 651, step: "South American Seafood Chowder In a large stock pot melt the butter with canola oil. Sweat the remaining 6 ingredients until soft about 5 minutes. Sprinkle in the fish bouillon Spanish paprika and cayenne pepper. Stir until coated - cook for 2-3 minutes to bring out the flavors of spices. Deglaze the pan with the white wine. Add in the coconut milk and heavy cream. Stir together and bring to a boil. Add in all the seafood and tomato paste simmer for 15-20 minutes. Clams and mussels should be opened. Taste season with salt and pepper as desired. Gently fold in the yucca (these will break easily which is okay) and allow to cook for 5 more minutes until it has been heated through. Ladle into 6 serving dishes...dividing up the seafood and yucca. This is a generous meal as it is rich and filling. Garnish with cilantro parsley and lime wedges.")
s.save!
s=Step.new(recipe_id: 652, step: "Directions for Pork: Combine the salt pepper and garlic powder. Rub on pork shoulder. Smoke the shoulder/butt for 6-8 hours or until porks internal temperature measures 195. If you braise the pork brown it on all sides in a dutch oven with 3 TBSP of oil until golden brown and then add 1 can beef broth and 1/2 can chicken broth. Bring to boil and put in a 350 oven for 3 hours or until pork starts to fall apart when a fork is run over the top of the butt. Let pork rest at least 1/2 hour and then pull/shred and set aside for addition to the chili. Directions for Chicken: Season chicken with salt and pepper. Roast over grill for 30 minutes turning half way through or bake in oven at 350 for 20 minutes or until internal temperature measures 160. Let rest 15 minutes and then pull off skin dispose skin and shred the meat into strips. Reserve until needed for chili. Directions for Chili: jalapenos and onions on a half sheet pan lined with foil turning until all sides are blistered and blackened. (It may take two pans to accommodate all the onions tomatillos and jalapenos.) Roast the garlic at the same time wrapped in aluminum foil with a splash of Extra Virgin Olive Oil salt and pepper. Remove the tomatillos onions and jalapenos from the oven. When cooled remove the skin from the jalapenos(s). Place the tomatillos onions garlic and jalapeno along with the juices from the roasting pan and place in batches into a blender and puree. Add the juice from half of the limes into the first batch that goes into the blender along with 1/3 of the cilantro and 1/2 of the roasted garlic squeezed out of the skins. Pour the puree into a large stock pot and repeat until all has been pureed. (You should have 1/3 of the cilantro left to add into the chili near the end of the cooking process.) Heat the large stockpot over medium heat containing the tomatillo cilantro onion garlic jalapeno puree. Add the dry spices cumin corriander black pepper garlic powder onion powder oregano and chipotle powder. Stir to combine. Next add shredded pork white beans black beans pinto beans corn tomatoes agave nectar or honey and salt. Stir once again to combine. Bring to a boil. Once boiling lower heat to a simmer. Simmer at least 3 hours to combine flavors. When chili is done simmer for at least 3 hours add in the shredded chicken breast and heat through about 5 minutes. Plate into bowl and serve.")
s.save!
s=Step.new(recipe_id: 653, step: "Spicy Sriracha Mayonnaise Combine mayonnaise lime juice and Sriracha sauce in a small bowl. Whisk until ingredients are completely combined. Cover and refrigerate until it is time to assemble the sandwich Coleslaw topping Finely shred cabbage in food processor. Remove cabbage from food processor and place in a large bowl. Mix cabbage the chopped cilantro rice vinegar and sesame oil until well combined. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Cook chicken breasts Heat olive oil and chili oil in skillet over medium high heat. Season both sides of chicken breast with salt and pepper. Saute chicken in hot skillet approximately 4 minutes on each side depending on the thickness of the chicken. During the last few minutes of cooking top chicken with slice of swiss cheese. Cheese will melt slightly. Chicken is done when juices run clear and chicken is firm to the touch.Remove chicken onto a plate lined with a paper towel. Sandwich assembly While chicken is cooking slice French bread into two six-inch long pieces. Half each piece and toast both top and bottom in toaster oven or under the broiler until lightly toasted. Liberally spread the lime-sriracha mayonnaise on both the top and bottom insides of the French bread. Place slices of avocado on bottom half of sandwich. Top with chicken. Top chicken with the Asian inspired coleslaw followed by ripe tomato slices and red onion. Top with bun slice in half and enjoy! Makes two six inch sandwiches.")
s.save!
s=Step.new(recipe_id: 654, step: "Easy Peasy--delish Directions: STEP 1: Preheat the oven to 180 (400 degrees f) Finely dice the onion and mince the garlic. Saut both in a skillet with olive oil until softened (about five minutes). STEP 2: While the onion and garlic are sauting thinly slice the rest of the vegetables. STEP 3: Spray the inside of an 8x8 square or round baking dish with non-stick spray. Spread the softened onion and garlic in the bottom of the dish. Place the thinly sliced vegetables in the baking dish vertically in an alternating pattern. Sprinkle generously with salt pepper and thyme. STEP 4: Cover the dish with foil and bake for 30 minutes. Remove the foil top with cheese and bake for another 15-20 minutes or until the cheese is golden brown")
s.save!
s=Step.new(recipe_id: 655, step: "step 1 Slice beef thinly. Peel onion cut the stem end off cut into half and slice each halved onion thinly. step 2 In a bowl mix together wasabi paste and soy sauce. step 3 In a skillet heat olive oil and cook garlic over medium heat until fragrant. Add onion and saut until onions are tender. Add beef and cook until beef are cooked through. Stir in soy sauce mixture and add salt and black pepper to taste. Toss to coat. Remove from the heat and set aside. step 4 Divide 8 tablespoons butter into four pieces (2 tablespoons for each) and cut each 4 pieces into three. step 5 Make grilled cheese sandwich one at a time. Melt 1/3 of 1 piece butter in a skillet over medium heat until foaming subsides. Add 2 bread slices and cook swirling occasionally until brown on bottom side. Put the bread on a cutting board cooked side up. Place beef onion mixture (drain the sauce) 2 slices cheese and put the other bread cooked side down to close sandwich. .Melt the other piece of butter in the same skillet and reduce heat to medium low heat. Add sandwich and cook swirling occasionally until golden brown. Take the sandwich out (put on a cutting board or plate) and add the remaining butter to the skillet. When the butter melts return sandwich to the skillet cooked side up. Cook swirling occasionally until second side is golden brown and cheese is thoroughly melted. step 6 Repeat this to make 3 more sandwiches.")
s.save!
s=Step.new(recipe_id: 656, step: "For Sriracha Mayonnaise Combine 1 teaspoon Sriracha and Mayonnaise in a small Bowl and stir to combine. Set aside. For Thai Red Curry Sauce Combine red curry paste coconut milk fish sauce and palm sugar in a small sauce pan. Cook over medium heat 8-10 minutes or until reduced by 1/3. Set aside. For Crispy Fried Shrimp Preheat oil in large sauce pan or fryer to 350 degrees. Set up three bowls for a dredging station. In the first bowl combine 1 cup AP Flour salt garlic powder and cayenne pepper. In the second bowl whisk the egg water sriracha and a pinch of salt. In the third bowl combine remaining 1/2 cup flour and panko bread crumbs. Dredge each shrimp in the flour then egg wash then panko mixture and set on a tray until finished dredging . Once the oil has reached 350 degrees fry shrimp 2-3 minutes or until golden brown. Drain on a rack. Place all of the cooked Shrimp into a large bowl and pour 1/4 - 1/2 cup of the Thai Red Curry Sauce over them. Toss to coat. For Slaw Combine purple and green cabbage red and green peppers red onions snap peas carrots and cilantro in a bowl. Squeeze juice of 1-2 limes over the vegetables and season with salt. Toss to coat and set aside. To Assemble Open one French Baguette and scoop out some of the bread inside. Lay a couple of pieces of green leaf lettuce on bottom then top with half of the sauced shrimp. Top with slaw and spread with Sriracha Mayonnaise on the top half of the baguette... Enjoy!")
s.save!
s=Step.new(recipe_id: 657, step: "step 1 Remove skin from salmon fillet cut into bite size put into a bowl and sprinkle salt and black pepper. Set aside. Chop green onions. step 2 Make sauce. In a bowl mix together green onions mayonnaise oyster sauce and soy sauce. step 3 In another bowl (medium-large) stir together rice flour and cornstarch. step 4 Heat safflower oil in a skillet or fry pan. Coat salmons with rice flour mixture and pan-fry salmons in the hot skillet/ fry pan until crisp and cooked through. Then drain on paper towels. stepr 5 Put the salmons into the sauce bowl and toss to coat. Fold in slice almond. Set aside. step 6 Halve avocado remove seed scoop avocado pulp and slice each halved avocado thinly. In another skillet melt butter over medium heat and saut avocadoes for 1-2 minutes. Season with salt and black pepper. step 7 Build sandwiches. On the bottom of croissant place 1/4 of sauted avocados and 1/4 of salmon mixture and put the top of croissant to close the sandwich. Repeat this to make 3 more sandwiches.")
s.save!
s=Step.new(recipe_id: 658, step: "Me & Mamas Fried Chicken with a twist Chicken - mixture of boneless chicken breast thighs and wings. Season the chicken the night before with a sprinkle of smoked sea salt fresh ground pepper smoked paprika pappys seasoning or you can substitute any other chicken season you may have. Dont over salt. Chop up a couple garlic gloves some fresh rosemary or dry and drizzle the chicken with some white truffle oil ( yes that is exactly what I said) give it try. Get a bowl mix eggs and milk together Sprinkle a little seasoning salt whatever kind you are using into the egg and milk mix and whisk it around. Now get that old cast iron skillet out or whatever type of frying cookware you may have. You can even use a deep fryer. Pour in some peanut oil. Its good for frying and its healthy. Throw a couple cloves into the skillet with the oil you will now when the oil is hot because those garlic gloves will start sizzling. Get your chicken ready; take one piece of chicken at a time and dredge in flour then the egg& mile mixture and oh yes the Panco. When that oil gets hot start placing your coated chicken into the skillet. Watch all the love that is going on; when that aroma floated around the house baby watch out. While your chicken is cooking your sides are well under way so when the chicken is done all your sides are as well. Your sides should be your favorite veggie homemade macaroni & cheese and a green leafy salad with some fresh basil chopped in it. By the time you call your loved ones to the table they will already be sitting there waiting. Enjoy your Sunday dinner. Thank you bkjiscooking4u")
s.save!
s=Step.new(recipe_id: 659, step: "Making the Salad Preparation Saut turkey bacon in heavy large skillet over medium heat until brown and crisp about 8 minutes Combine chopped eggs celery and olives in bowl. Mix in 1/4 cup mayonnaise and mustard. No need for salt in this recipe the olives are salty in their brine Place toast slices on work surface. Divide egg salad among 6 toast slices. Place bacon then arugula leaves atop egg salad on each. Cover with remaining toast slices mayonnaise side down. Cut sandwiches and devour")
s.save!
s=Step.new(recipe_id: 660, step: "Step 1 Mix brown sugar margarine eggs vanilla cream of tartar and salt in mixer on medium. Than as my mother says beat the heck out of it on high until creamy (roughly 5 minutes) Step 2 Reduce mixer speed to lowest setting and add in baking soda. It is important to keep the mixer at a slow setting as you dont want to over mix the baking soda. Then add in the first 4 cups of flour in the mixer. Turn off the mixer and mix in the final 2 cups by hand until the flour is mixed into the dough. Step 3 Refrigerate the dough up to 1 hour Step 4 Roll out the dough to about 1/4 inch thickness. Use your favorite cookie cutter shape and in our case it is a Gingerman Step 5 Decorate your cookie design with your favorite toppings. In our case we use pecans as the hands and feet of the Gingerman and Chocolate Chips as the eyes and buttons Step 6 Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350 for 10 minutes or until brown but not dry. Let cook for 15 minutes and enjoy.")
s.save!